This paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for medical data analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on energy cost effectiveness and computational efficiency suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV), as these fields often deal with resource-constrained environments. The use of Bayesian compression techniques may also make the paper relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
